SIMPLE: metameric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metameric
<hw>Met`a*mer"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>meta-</ets> + Gr. <?/ part.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Having the same molecular formula, but possessing a different
bonding structure and different properties; <as>as, methyl ether and
ethyl alcohol are <ex>metameric</ex> compounds</as>. See
<er>Isomeric</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The existence of metameric compounds is due to different
arrangements of the same atoms in the molecule.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a metamere or
its formation; <as>as, <ex>metameric</ex> segmentation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metamerically</ent>⟦br⟧
